So they show precisely how you start with an amplitude hydrant

33:11.760 --> 33:17.600
and how you project this high-dimensional structure into the four dimensions of space time.

33:18.240 --> 33:22.240
So there's a precise procedure that relates the two.

33:22.240 --> 33:25.040
And they're doing the same thing with the cosmological polytopes.

33:25.600 --> 33:32.800
So they're the ones that are making the most concrete and fun advances going beyond space time.

33:32.800 --> 33:34.400
And they're tethering it.

33:35.200 --> 33:40.960
They say this is precisely the mathematical projection from this deeper structure into space time.

33:41.760 --> 33:46.800
One thing I'll say about, as a nonphysicist, what I find interesting is that they're finding just

33:47.600 --> 33:50.320
geometry, but there's no notion of dynamics.

33:51.040 --> 33:54.960
Right now, they're just finding these static geometric structures,

33:55.840 --> 33:57.120
which is impressive.

33:57.120 --> 33:58.240
So I'm not putting them down.

33:58.240 --> 34:05.440
This is what they're doing is unbelievably complicated and brilliant and adventurous.

34:07.280 --> 34:08.160
It's all those things.

34:08.160 --> 34:12.800
And beautiful from a human aesthetic perspective because geometry is beautiful.

34:12.800 --> 34:14.000
It's absolutely.

34:14.000 --> 34:17.680
And they're finding symmetries that are true of the data that can't be seen in space time.

34:18.640 --> 34:24.160
But I'm looking for a theory beyond space time that's a dynamical theory.

34:25.120 --> 34:29.840
I would love to find, and we can talk about that at some point, a theory of consciousness in which

34:30.800 --> 34:36.320
the dynamics of consciousness itself will give rise to the geometry that the physicists are

34:36.320 --> 34:37.760
finding beyond space time.

34:37.760 --> 34:41.520
If we can do that, then we'd have a completely different way of looking at how consciousness

34:41.520 --> 34:46.160
is related to what we call the brain or the physical world more generally.

34:46.240 --> 34:51.360
Right now, all of my brilliant colleagues, about 99% of them, are trying to...

34:53.920 --> 34:55.600
